      • getPropertyNames

        public Set<String> getPropertyNames()
        Deprecated.
        Returns an unmodifiable and unchanging Set of Strings representing the names of properties whose values may be retrieved with the getProperty(String, String) method.

        This method never returns null.

        Overrides of this method must not return null.

        Overrides of this method must ensure that the Set returned may be used without the end user having to peform explicit synchronization.

        This method and its overrides, if any, may return the same Set instance with each invocation, or different Set instances with different contents.

        Specified by:

      • getProperty

        public String getProperty​(String propertyName,
                          String defaultValue)
        Deprecated.
        Returns a value for the property described by the supplied propertyName, or the value of the supplied defaultValue parameter if no such property value exists.

        This method will return null if defaultValue is null.

        Overrides of this method may return null if defaultValue is null.

        This method and its overrides, if any, may return the same or different values for each invocation with the same parameters.

        Specified by:
        getProperty in class ServiceConfiguration
        Parameters:

        defaultValue - the value to return if a value for the named property could not be found; may be null
